################################################################################
# MVP 6 — THIRD-PARTY API INTEGRATION & PROJECT COST PLANNING
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Integrate all external APIs + document complete project cost breakdown
# Budget Reference (from image): Domain ₹1,900 | Backend ₹5,000 | Frontend ₹4,000
#                                 Third-party API ₹3,500
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: File Storage API Integration
[ ] Choose cloud storage provider: AWS S3 / Cloudinary / Firebase Storage
[ ] Install SDK (AWS SDK v3 / cloudinary npm package)
[ ] Configure credentials in .env:
    [ ] STORAGE_PROVIDER=s3
    [ ] S3_BUCKET_NAME=
    [ ] S3_REGION=
    [ ] AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
    [ ] AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
[ ] Create storage service utility (`/services/storage.service.js`):
    [ ] `uploadFile(fileBuffer, fileName, folder)` → returns public URL
    [ ] `deleteFile(fileKey)` → removes file from cloud
    [ ] `getSignedUrl(fileKey, expiresIn)` → returns time-limited URL for private files
[ ] Apply to: Resume uploads, Company logos, User avatars
[ ] Set bucket/folder structure:
    [ ] /resumes/{userId}/{uuid}.pdf
    [ ] /avatars/{userId}/avatar.jpg
    [ ] /logos/{recruiterId}/logo.png
[ ] Set CORS policy on S3 bucket (allow frontend domain only)
[ ] Enable versioning on resume bucket (keep old versions on re-upload)
[ ] Estimated cost: Free tier (5GB storage, 20,000 GET/PUT per month on AWS S3)

## PHASE 2: OpenAI API Integration
[ ] Install: `npm install openai` (official Node.js SDK v4+)
[ ] Configure in .env:
    [ ] OPENAI_API_KEY=
    [ ] OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini  (cost-optimized)
    [ ] OPENAI_MAX_TOKENS=2000
[ ] Create OpenAI service wrapper (`/services/openai.service.js`):
    [ ] `callOpenAI(prompt, systemPrompt, maxTokens)` → returns string response
    [ ] `callOpenAIJson(prompt, systemPrompt)` → returns parsed JSON object
    [ ] Handle: RateLimitError, APITimeoutError, APIConnectionError (retry 3x)
    [ ] Log: model used, tokens consumed, cost estimate per call
[ ] Implement cost tracking:
    [ ] gpt-4o-mini: $0.15/1M input tokens, $0.60/1M output tokens
    [ ] Estimate 500 resumes/month × 2,000 tokens = 1M tokens ~ $0.30/month
    [ ] Estimate 5,000 job matches/month × 1,500 tokens = 7.5M tokens ~ $1.50/month
    [ ] Total AI cost estimate: ~₹300-400/month well within ₹3,500 budget
[ ] Implement monthly quota enforcement (hard stop at ₹2,500 to have buffer):
    [ ] Check monthly usage (from MongoDB AiUsageLog) before each AI call
    [ ] If quota exceeded: log warning, fall back to keyword matching
    [ ] Alert admin via email when 80% of monthly budget is reached

## PHASE 3: Email Notification API Integration
[ ] Choose email provider: Resend / SendGrid / AWS SES (Resend recommended for simplicity)
[ ] Install: resend npm package
[ ] Configure in .env:
    [ ] EMAIL_PROVIDER=resend
    [ ] RESEND_API_KEY=
    [ ] EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
[ ] Create email service (`/services/email.service.js`):
    [ ] `sendEmail(to, subject, htmlBody)` → generic email sender
    [ ] `sendWelcomeEmail(user)` → triggered on signup
    [ ] `sendApplicationConfirmation(user, job)` → triggered on apply
    [ ] `sendStatusUpdateEmail(user, job, newStatus)` → triggered on status change
    [ ] `sendJobMatchNotification(user, topJobs)` → weekly digest
[ ] Design email templates (HTML + inline CSS):
    [ ] Welcome email template (with CTA: Complete your profile)
    [ ] Application confirmation template
    [ ] Status update template (shortlisted / rejected / interview invite)
    [ ] Weekly job match recommendations template
[ ] Implement email queue using Bull (don't block API response with email sending)
[ ] Estimated cost: Resend free tier: 3,000 emails/month → FREE
    [ ] Paid plan if needed: $20/month for 50,000 emails

## PHASE 4: Webhook / Real-time Notifications (Optional)
[ ] Implement server-sent events (SSE) OR WebSocket (socket.io) for real-time dashboard updates:
    [ ] User gets notified instantly when:
        [ ] Application status changes
        [ ] AI resume analysis completes
    [ ] Recruiter gets notified when:
        [ ] New applicant applies for their job
[ ] Implement in-app notification model:
    [ ] Create `Notification` Mongoose schema: userId (ref), type, message, isRead, createdAt
[ ] GET /api/notifications → list unread notifications
[ ] PATCH /api/notifications/:id/read → mark as read
[ ] PATCH /api/notifications/read-all → mark all as read

## PHASE 5: LinkedIn OAuth Integration (Optional Enhancement)
[ ] Register app on LinkedIn Developer Portal
[ ] Configure OAuth 2.0 credentials:
    [ ] LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID=
    [ ] LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET=
    [ ] LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI=
[ ] Add "Sign in with LinkedIn" button on login/signup page
[ ] On OAuth callback:
    [ ] Fetch user's LinkedIn profile (name, email, picture, headline)
    [ ] Pre-fill signup form with LinkedIn data
    [ ] Auto-import LinkedIn skills into candidate profile

## PHASE 6: Analytics API Integration (Optional)
[ ] Integrate Google Analytics 4 or Plausible (privacy-focused):
    [ ] Track page views, user flows, conversion funnel
    [ ] Events: signup_completed, resume_uploaded, job_applied, ai_score_viewed
[ ] Recruiter analytics (internal):
    [ ] Job views, application rate, shortlist rate per job
    [ ] Average match score distribution chart

## PHASE 7: Complete Project Cost Breakdown
[ ] Document all costs:

    --- DOMAIN ---
    [ ] Register domain (.com / .in / .tech): ₹1,900/year
        Options: GoDaddy, Namecheap, Google Domains

    --- FRONTEND HOSTING ---
    [ ] Vercel (free tier → auto-upgrades only if needed): ₹0 initially
        [ ] Custom domain setup on Vercel: ₹0
    [ ] Development cost (UI/UX + React): ₹4,000

    --- BACKEND HOSTING ---
    [ ] Render.com Web Service (Node.js): Free tier available (spins down on inactivity)
        [ ] Upgrade to Starter (~₹1,200/month) for always-on production backend
    [ ] Development cost (API + DB): ₹5,000

    --- DATABASE ---
    [ ] MongoDB Atlas (Free M0 cluster: 512MB storage) → ₹0 for MVP
        [ ] Upgrade to M2 Shared (~₹1,200/month) if data exceeds free tier
    [ ] Redis (for Bull queue): Upstash Redis free tier (~10,000 req/day) → ₹0

    --- THIRD-PARTY APIS ---
    [ ] OpenAI API budget: ₹3,500
        [ ] Estimated monthly AI usage: ₹300-600 (leaves buffer)
    [ ] AWS S3 (file storage): Free tier covers initial usage
    [ ] Resend email: Free tier (3,000 emails/month)

    --- DOCUMENTATION COSTS ---
    [ ] API documentation (Swagger/Postman collection): ₹0 (use free tools)
    [ ] Project Book Binding (printed report): ~₹500-1,000
    [ ] PPT Presentation design: ₹0 (use Canva free)

    --- TOTAL ESTIMATED PROJECT COST (ONE-TIME + 1ST MONTH) ---
    [ ] Domain: ₹1,900
    [ ] Backend dev: ₹5,000
    [ ] Frontend dev: ₹4,000
    [ ] API Integration: ₹3,500
    [ ] Documentation (binding + PPT): ₹1,000
    [ ] GRAND TOTAL: ~₹15,400

